VThis album from one of the front-ranking Carnatic flautists has a collection of 10 kritis by various composers, including the Trinity &#8211; the Begada varnam of Patnam Subramania Iyer; Tyagaraja's &#8216;Nadichi Naichi' (Kharaharapriya) and &#8216;Bhajare' (Kanada), Dikshitar's &#8216;Gajanana' (Chakravakam), Swati Tirunal's &#8216;Parama Purusha' (Vasantha) and &#8216;Thunga Taranga' (Behag). Call 24752802 or email: info@adityamusicindia.com.***For this album, the sisters have chosen popular kritis on Lord Siva by various composers. Listen to the magical words of Muthu Thandavar (&#8216;Maravaathiru Nenjamae'), Papanasam Sivan (Kapali, &#8216;Kaana Kann Kodi Vendum'), Ambujam Krishna (&#8216;Shambo Mahadeva'), Tyagaraja (&#8216;Siva Siva Ena Rada') and Periasami Thooran (&#8216;Pichchai Edukka Vandha'). ***Part of the classical series, this presentation has the magical voice of D.K. Pattammal, the soulful Maharajapuram Santhanam, Madurai T.N. Seshagopalan, Bombay Sisters, Nithyasree Mahadevan, Priya Sisters and Unnikrishnan.***The genius of maestro is here for Hindustani music lovers and Joshi fans to absorb in this album. He presents evening raag Vrindavani Sarang and the popular &#8216;Ab ke Saawan' (thumri) in this pack. He is accompanied by Srinivas Joshi (vocal support), Bharat Kamat (tabla), Sudhir Naik (harmonium) and Ashutosh Mukherjee (tanpura).
